// ============================================================================
// WHY THIS WAS DISABLED:
// Skyrim VR's IVRRenderModels shader implementation doesn't properly apply
// UV-mapped textures. It expects a simple flat color texture (1x1 pixel).
// When given a real UV-mapped texture like the Quest 3 controller PNGs,
// the shader renders the models as solid black silhouettes.
//
// To fix this would require either:
// 1. Patching Skyrim's shader to support UV mapping
// 2. Generating a solid-color texture from the PNG's average color
// 3. Using a different rendering path that bypasses IVRRenderModels
// ============================================================================

